<tr id="L299"><td><a href="#L299">299</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  (pulsing green) That is not true, Captain. Once we had humanoid form, but we evolved beyond it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L300"><td><a href="#L300">300</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  (yellow) Through eons of devoting ourselves exclusively to intellectual pursuits, we became the physically simple, mentally superior creatures you see before you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L301"><td><a href="#L301">301</a></td><td>KIRK:  A species that enslaves other beings is hardly superior, mentally or otherwise.</td></tr>

<tr id="L302"><td><a href="#L302">302</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  The thralls are necessary to the games. We have found athletic competitions our only challenge, the only thing which furnishes us with purpose.</td></tr>

<tr id="L303"><td><a href="#L303">303</a></td><td>KIRK:  It's an unproductive purpose, unworthy of your intellect.</td></tr>

<tr id="L304"><td><a href="#L304">304</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  We use only inferior beings.</td></tr>

<tr id="L305"><td><a href="#L305">305</a></td><td>KIRK:  We have found that all life forms in the galaxy are capable of superior development. Perhaps you're not as evolved as you believe.</td></tr>

<tr id="L306"><td><a href="#L306">306</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  An interesting speculation, Captain. You and your people are most challenging.</td></tr>

<tr id="L307"><td><a href="#L307">307</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  Yes, most challenging. It was hoped that such new blood would stimulate our stock of thralls. How unfortunate that you must be destroyed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L308"><td><a href="#L308">308</a></td><td>KIRK:  Our destruction will result only in your own. You may control the Enterprise, but you cannot match the force of the entire Federation.</td></tr>

<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Your ship will be destroyed by a magnetic storm. No communications with your base will be possible. Your fate will remain a mystery to your people.</td></tr>

<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>KIRK:  And you call yourselves superior! You're murderers without the spirit to really wager for the lives you take.</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Wager? Explain yourself, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>KIRK:  My people pride themselves on being the greatest, most successful gamblers in the universe. We compete for everything. Power, fame, women, everything we desire, and it is our nature to win. And for proof, I offer you our exploration of this galaxy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  We are aware of your competitive abilities, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, then, I wager that with weapons of your own choice, right here and now, my people can overcome an equal number of thralls set against us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  A hundred quatloos on the newcomers.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Four hundred quatloos against the newcomers.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  Two hundred quatloos against!</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  Five hundred for the newcomers. Contest by multiple elimination.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>KIRK:  Wait! Wait! Hear me! We can't wager for trifles like quatloos. The stakes must be higher.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Name your stakes, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>KIRK:  If we win, the Enterprise and its crew leaves here in safety. Further more, all the thralls on the planet must be freed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  Anarchy. They would starve.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>KIRK:  You will educate and train them to establish a normal self-governing culture.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  Thralls govern themselves? Ridiculous!</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>KIRK:  We have done the same with cultures throughout the galaxy. Are you willing to admit that we can do something you can't?</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  There is nothing we cannot do!</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  And if you lose, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>KIRK:  If we lose? We will remain here, the entire crew of the Enterprise. The most stubborn, determined competitors in the universe. We'll become thralls, enter your games, obey your orders without rebellion. You'll be assured of generations of the most exciting wagering you've ever had.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Your stakes are indeed high, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>KIRK:  Not for true gamesters.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>THREE [OC]:  We will accept your stakes on one condition.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>KIRK:  Name it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  As leader of your people, your spirit seems most indomitable. We suggest you alone, pitted against three contestants of our choosing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>KIRK:  Three against one? Those are pretty high odds.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>TWO [OC]:  Not for true gamesters, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>KIRK:  Your, your terms are unfair.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  On the contrary, they're extremely fair, since your alternative is death.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, in that case, I'll accept your terms.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Galt will prepare you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Combat area</td></tr>
<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Lars has a net, Kloog has his whip, and an Andorian has the pole weapon, same as Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Because you wager your skill for all your people, they will be permitted to watch the outcome of the game on the ship's viewscreen.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Mister Spock, look!</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  Captain, you will defend. Thralls must stay in the blue area. You will take the yellow. Touching an opposing colour deprives a contestant of one weapon. An opponent must be killed to be removed from the game. If only wounded, he is replaced by a fresh thrall. Is that clear, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Combat area</td></tr>
<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, that's clear.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What in the name of heaven is this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Heaven's got very little to do with this.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Combat area</td></tr>
<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: So the fight begins, and everyone puts their feet outside their allotted colours from time to time. Kirk manages to trip up or push over each of his three opponents several times. Eventually he throws his pole into Kloog's belly then picks up a dagger to defend himself with. Lars traps his hand in the net, but Kirk ducks as the Andorian throws his pole. Now the two fight with just the daggers, until Kirk throws the Andorian. Galt sees that he is only injured, and orders in his replacement.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>GALT:  Shahna.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She enters the area with a pole.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  You lied. Everything you said.</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: She trips him, but he grabs the pole and pulls her down to the point of his dagger. They both hesitate, break free, and she gets him at her mercy. Again there is hesitation, so Kirk uses his legs to grab her and this time puts the blade firmly to her throat.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  The thralls surrender!</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk lets her go.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  You have won, Captain Kirk, unfortunately. However, the terms of the wager will be honoured. You are free. Remove your collars.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They come off easily.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>KIRK:  The thralls will be trained?</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>ONE [OC]:  They will be trained. We have said it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>KIRK:  I think you'll find it a much more exciting game than the one you've been playing. I'm sorry, Shahna. I didn't lie. I did what was necessary. Someday, I hope you'll understand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  I understand, a little. You will leave us now?</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  To go back to the lights in the sky?</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  I would like to go to those lights with you. Take me?</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>KIRK:  I can't.</td></tr>

<tr id="L365"><td><a href="#L365">365</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  Then teach me how, and I will follow you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L366"><td><a href="#L366">366</a></td><td>KIRK:  There's so much you must learn here first. The Providers will teach you. Learn it, Shahna. all your people must learn before you can reach for the stars. Shahna. (he gives her a farewell kiss) Scotty!</td></tr>

<tr id="L367"><td><a href="#L367">367</a></td><td>SCOTT [OC]:  Aye, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L368"><td><a href="#L368">368</a></td><td>KIRK:  Beam us up.</td></tr>

<tr id="L369"><td><a href="#L369">369</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They disappear in a twinkle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L370"><td><a href="#L370">370</a></td><td>SHAHNA:  Goodbye, Jim Kirk. I will learn, and watch the lights in the sky, and remember.</td></tr>

